ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Following the identification of highly pathogenic influenza virus
(HPAI) virus strain H5N1, Indonesia has today (Tue, 3 Feb 2004)
officially notified the OIE about 127 outbreaks in 57 districts
within 10 provinces; estimated date of primary infection, according
to this notification, was 11 Dec 2003.
The following 7 Asian countries have so far officially notified HPAI
caused by H5N1 (date of first notification in brackets):
Korea (Rep. of) : 12 Dec 2003
Vietnam : 9 Jan 2004
Japan : 13 Jan 2004
Thailand : 23 Jan 2004
Cambodia : 24 Jan 2004
Laos : 27 Jan 2004
Indonesia : 3 Feb 2004
Pakistan and Taiwan have recorded other avian influenza virus
strains. No notification has been forthcoming from China.
The OIE is providing a table with dates of initial and follow-up
notifications, updated 3 Feb 2004, at
<http://oie.int/downld/AVIAN%20INFLUENZA/A_AI-Asia.htm>. - Mod.AS].
